WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-RU

00:00:00.200 --> 00:00:01.334
With Return of the Ancients,

00:00:01.334 --> 00:00:05.672
we're adding a
challenge series to the Path of Exile 2 league for the first time.

00:00:05.672 --> 00:00:07.574
For every two challenges you complete,

00:00:07.574 --> 00:00:10.193
you'll receive a piece of the Aldur Knight armor set,

00:00:10.193 --> 00:00:11.795
so it's worth trying to complete them.

00:00:12.362 --> 00:00:15.148
To check your progress and
the requirements for completing a challenge,

00:00:15.148 --> 00:00:17.801
simply press "H" to open the Challenges screen.  There are

00:00:17.951 --> 00:00:19.319
eight challenges in total,

00:00:19.319 --> 00:00:22.222
and they gradually increase in difficulty from
fairly easy to quite challenging.

00:00:22.222 --> 00:00:23.923
To complete the Runeseeker challenge,

00:00:23.923 --> 00:00:26.626
you'll need to find relics with
ever-increasing sockets

00:00:26.626 --> 00:00:28.595
and use them to craft new items.

00:00:29.229 --> 00:00:32.999
Using the seven nests can be
quite challenging due to the six waves of enemies,

00:00:32.999 --> 00:00:36.002
so attempting to fight in such an event
may require some skill.  There

00:00:38.638 --> 00:00:39.639


00:00:39.639 --> 00:00:41.408
are many optional bosses throughout the campaign.

00:00:41.408 --> 00:00:42.959
To complete the Hunter challenge,

00:00:42.959 --> 00:00:45.361
you will need to track down six of them.

00:00:45.361 --> 00:00:49.282
The last two, Akthi, the Last Sting,
and Anundr, the Sandworm,

00:00:49.282 --> 00:00:51.551
can be quite difficult to reach in Kharian Pass.

00:00:52.185 --> 00:00:55.271
To find them, follow the
dry river bed.

00:00:55.388 --> 00:00:57.073
You will find the arena with them at the end.

00:00:58.558 --> 00:01:00.877
To complete the Ascended challenge,
you need to earn all eight points of

00:01:00.877 --> 00:01:03.880
your Ascension class by
completing Ascension challenges.

00:01:03.880 --> 00:01:06.766
However, getting the final
score can be quite difficult.

00:01:06.766 --> 00:01:10.220
You will need to either defeat
Zarok in Level 4 of the Trial of Sekhem,

00:01:10.653 --> 00:01:14.390
or defeat the Trial Master in
the Trial of Chaos, finding all three keys.

00:01:15.141 --> 00:01:16.960
Of the two trials, the Trial of Chaos will

00:01:16.960 --> 00:01:20.029
take you much longer
since you will have to complete it multiple times,

00:01:20.029 --> 00:01:22.549
but the Trial of Sekhem is more difficult,

00:01:22.549 --> 00:01:25.151
so you will have to decide
which of the two paths to take.  The

00:01:26.719 --> 00:01:28.138
Reliquarian test is simple.

00:01:28.138 --> 00:01:30.573
Identify 50 different unique items.

00:01:32.025 --> 00:01:33.910
Having trouble finding unique items?

00:01:33.910 --> 00:01:37.647
Jado, the Master of Atlas, has a variety of
abilities that specialize in finding them.

00:01:39.749 --> 00:01:41.151
To complete the Craftsman challenge,

00:01:41.151 --> 00:01:43.720
you will need to use a variety of
different crafting items.

00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:45.839
All of them are obtained in battles near relics.

00:01:47.240 --> 00:01:48.441
For the Cartographer challenge,

00:01:48.441 --> 00:01:50.894
you will need to distribute points
across your entire Atlas tree.

00:01:51.177 --> 00:01:52.712
All 300 nodes.

00:01:53.163 --> 00:01:56.883
You can do this the slow way by
going through all the maps inside the fortress.

00:01:56.916 --> 00:01:58.918
But there is another way.

00:01:58.918 --> 00:02:01.054
Each time you defeat the Divine Arbiter,

00:02:01.054 --> 00:02:05.175
you gain the ability to automatically
clear a large section of the fortress.

00:02:06.676 --> 00:02:09.679
Find the keys to fighting him by searching Citadels in the Atlas.

00:02:09.829 --> 00:02:12.832
Each of them has large glowing beams
so you can see them in the fog.

00:02:13.032 --> 00:02:16.719
After four battles with him, the entire
fortress will be completed.

00:02:17.871 --> 00:02:21.040
And last but not least, the Winner.

00:02:21.391 --> 00:02:24.010
This challenge requires killing
three high-level bosses,

00:02:24.010 --> 00:02:25.478
the most difficult in the game:

00:02:25.979 --> 00:02:27.030
Tangmazu,

00:02:27.030 --> 00:02:28.097
Bodakh, and

00:02:28.097 --> 00:02:29.682
the Vessel of Kulemak.

00:02:30.083 --> 00:02:34.070
These are the highbosses of Delirium, Ritual, and Abyss,

00:02:34.070 --> 00:02:37.190
so you'll need to complete those three
questlines to complete this challenge.

00:02:37.674 --> 00:02:39.909
However, it is important to remember that with the Vessel of Kulemak

00:02:39.909 --> 00:02:42.162
you need to defeat him at full strength.

00:02:42.162 --> 00:02:44.113
This means risking
the item during a boss fight by

00:02:44.113 --> 00:02:46.716
getting the finger back and still defeating the boss.

00:02:49.352 --> 00:02:50.303
As I mentioned,

00:02:50.303 --> 00:02:53.223
for every two quests you complete, you'll
receive pieces of an armor set,

00:02:53.223 --> 00:02:55.675
so you don't have to complete
all the challenges to get the rewards.

00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:58.628
But if you do, you'll be able to
show off your skill

00:02:58.778 --> 00:03:02.715
because everyone in the global chat or on the forums
will be able to see how many challenges you've completed.

00:03:03.149 --> 00:03:05.835
You'll also get this totem
as a decoration for your hideout,

00:03:05.835 --> 00:03:07.837
meaning even more people
who trade with you

00:03:07.837 --> 00:03:10.840
will be able to see that you
were there and beat the league.

00:03:11.191 --> 00:03:15.361
Try these quests and
more on May 29th in Return of the Ancients.

00:03:15.562 --> 00:03:17.463
Thanks for watching and see you there!

